    <dc:description>
      <abstract original="y" xml:lang="eng"> <ce:para>Based on case-analysis methodology, the paper studies what relevance the activity of communicating learning results to students after a written test may have for knowledge building in the classroom. This analysis allows us to identify the educational mechanisms used by the teacher to turn the test assessment into a mediating tool to improve learning; also, to know how the teacher and students jointly build the meaning of the assessment and learning, and progressively shares with them a specific conception of both. © 2007 by Fundación Infancia y Aprendizaje.</ce:para> </abstract>
